Package io.artframework

Interface ArtLoader

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Scoped
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ArtParser<TParser,​TInput>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultArtLoader, DefaultArtParser
    public interface ArtLoader
extends Scoped
    The art loader is responsible for loading a config type into an art context.

    It can be configured with various parsers that parse the input into an ArtContext.

      • parser

        <TParser extends Parser<TInput>,​TInput> ArtLoader parser​(java.lang.Class<TParser> parserClass,
                                                               java.util.function.Function<Scope,​TParser> parser)
        Registers the given parser class and supplier as an ArtParser that can be used to create art contexts.

        Make sure that your implementing parser is immutable and only performs atomic operations without side effects.

        The same parser instance may be called with multiple inputs.

        Type Parameters:
        TParser - the type of the parser
        TInput - the input the parser accepts
        Parameters:
        parserClass - the class of the parser that should be registered
        parser - the parser that is registered
        Returns:
        this art loader instance

      • parser

        <TParser extends Parser<TInput>,​TInput> TParser parser​(java.lang.Class<TParser> parserClass)
        Gets a registered parser for the given parser class.

        Returns null if no parser with the class is registered.

        Type Parameters:
        TParser - the type of the parser
        TInput - the type of the input
        Parameters:
        parserClass - the class of the parser
        Returns:
        a new instance of the given parser or null if no parser is registered

      • parse

        default ArtContext parse​(java.util.Collection<java.lang.String> strings)
                  throws ParseException
        Directly parses the given string list using the default flow parser.
        Parameters:
        strings - the list of strings in flow syntax notation
        Returns:
        the parsed ArtContext
        Throws:
        ParseException - if the provided list of strings cannot be parsed into an art context.

        This can be the case if an art-object is missing or the syntax is incorrect.
